This paper deals with the analysis of scholarly papers and their citation network, which falls under the scope of several sub-categories in computer science. The use of electric network models to estimate thematic similarity suggests that the paper may be related to topics such as social networks, information retrieval, and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
